<br>
A new group has appeared in Norrath (and on Luclin as well). Rumor has it that these 'Soulbinders' have dedicated themselves to research on the power and essence of our inner being. Some call them fanatics, as they claim that knowledge of the spirit that dwells within will lead them to an understanding of the whole of existence. Citizens often treat them with the same respect and distance that they treat the Priests of Discord. However, these Soulbinders have dedicated themselves to public service, and for them that service falls along their lines of specialty...<br>
<br>
The next time you find yourself far away from home, you might seek the services of a Soulbinder.<br>
<br>
/ooc: We've added these "Soulbinder" NPCs to all cities that player characters can start in, as well as Shadowhaven and Iceclad at the request of players. It is our hope that these new NPCs will help players by reducing the time it takes to find a bind from another player character.<br>
<br>
Tod <br>
<br>
---------------<br>
<br>
((pro: i'm a shy person and hate begging for a bind.  fortunately, most places i go i can depend on a sister for a handy bind.  but i've played for hours on the moon, still bound to some ridiculously far location, because the moon is fairly sparse on binders sometimes.  <br>
<br>
con: on servers like FV where even casters are restricted to melee bind locations, the introduction of this makes their binding skills almost redundant.  why donate platinum to a PC when you can bind for free, and without having to ask?  (well, aside from the obvious - it's a nice way to help a caster.)  it's probably too soon to see what the real effect of this may be, but it's...interesting...  up next, NPC porters!)) <p><img src=http://publish.hometown.aol.com/ayaekitenshi/myhomepage/eyeburn_logo.gif></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ayanamiiekitenshi>Ayanamii Ekitenshi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ayaekitenshi.freeservers.com/images/blink.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/21/01 5:43:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bridh>Bridh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sister</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#660000>(12/21/01 6:38:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=170.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ((nerf!))</span><hr size=1> I actually heard that it wasn't free.<br>
